decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to aggressively use a combination of cards to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy while maintaining a strong board presence. With cards like Thoughtseize and Fatal Push to control the opponent's hand and board state, and powerful creatures like Sheoldred, the Apocalypse and Ketramose, the New Dawn to dominate the battlefield, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents quickly. Additionally, the use of graveyard manipulation with Necrodominance and Relic of Progenitus adds another layer of disruption to ensure victory in a 1 vs 1 Modern format.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy while building up a board presence with aggressive creatures. The deck utilizes a combination of removal spells like Fatal Push and Solitude, along with disruptive cards like Thoughtseize and Relic of Progenitus. The deck also includes creatures with powerful abilities such as Flickerwisp and Emperor of Bones, as well as synergistic cards like Ephemerate and Boggart Trawler. By controlling the game with disruption and aggressive threats, the deck aims to outpace and overwhelm the opponent to secure victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing creatures with cycling abilities to fill up the graveyard and then cast Living End to return all creatures from the graveyard to the battlefield. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Force of Negation and Subtlety to control the game until the Living End combo can be executed. By cycling through cards and manipulating the graveyard, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a massive board presence in a single turn, often leading to a quick victory through overwhelming force.

This deck focuses on quickly ramping up mana and generating powerful combo plays using cards like Primeval Titan, Simic Growth Chamber, and Scapeshift to search for key lands and overwhelm the opponent with large creatures. The key strategy is to efficiently tutor for the necessary pieces and accelerate the game plan to quickly assemble a dominating board state. The deck leverages the Amulet of Vigor to further enhance the mana ramping capabilities and enable explosive plays. Ultimately, the goal is to overwhelm the opponent with overwhelming board presence and outpace their defenses.

This deck utilizes the Underworld Breach combo to repeatedly cast spells from the graveyard, using cards like Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student to fuel the engine. Grinding Station helps to mill cards for the combo, while Mishra's Bauble and Malevolent Rumble provide additional value and disruption. The deck also includes different lands for flexibility and protection, as well as a variety of spells for interaction and win conditions, such as Thassa's Oracle for instant victory. Overall, the focus is on assembling the combo pieces and executing a game-winning sequence.

The main concept of this deck is to utilize a landless combo strategy to win the game. The deck focuses on using cards like Goblin Charbelcher and Hydroelectric Specimen to deal damage directly to the opponent without needing to rely on traditional land drops. Disrupting Shoal and Flare of Denial provide disruption against opponent's spells, while Thundertrap Trainer and Tameshi, Reality Architect help control the board. The deck also includes card draw and tutor effects like Whir of Invention and Sea Gate Restoration to ensure consistency in executing the combo.

The main idea behind this deck is to utilize cards like Indomitable Creativity and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker to combo off and cheat powerful creatures like Archon of Cruelty into play. This deck aims to be creative in its approach, using cards like Faithless Looting and Expressive Iteration to dig for combo pieces while disrupting the opponent with cards like Thoughtseize and Lightning Bolt. The deck also includes a mix of removal spells like Fatal Push and Spell Pierce to control the board and protect the combo.
